### 1. CRITICAL: Remove postingDate from the Bulk Upload Payload
In the VoucherBulkUpload component at the top of your code, your autoSubmitBatch function is **still sending postingDate**. If this field does not exist in your Spring Boot DTO, **ST will crash** with that exact same MismatchedInputException!
**Find this block in VoucherBulkUpload (around line 300):**
```javascript
       const payload = {
        requestId: reqId,
        postingDate: selectedDate.format("DD/MM/YYYY"), // <-- REMOVE THIS LINE!
        vid: currentVid, 
        commonBatchRemarks: "Voucher created successfully",
      };

```
**Replace it entirely with this strict, ST-safe payload:**
```javascript
       const payload = {
        requestId: reqId,
        vid: currentVid, 
        commonBatchRemarks: "Voucher created successfully",
      };

```
